
links:https://newpush.com/2011/10/how-to-install-tomcat-6-on-rhel-6-or-centos-6/



installing tomcat


1.yum install yum-priorities
2.rpm -Uvh http://apt.sw.be/redhat/el6/en/x86_64/rpmforge/RPMS/rpmforge-release-0.5.2-2.el6.rf.x86_64.rpm
3.rpm -Uvh http://download.fedora.redhat.com/pub/epel/6/x86_64/epel-release-6-5.noarch.rpm
4.rpm -Uvh http://mirrors.dotsrc.org/jpackage/6.0/generic/free/RPMS/jpackage-utils-5.0.0-7.jpp6.noarch.rpm
5.yum -y install java
6.yum -y install tomcat6 tomcat6-webapps tomcat6-admin-webapps
7.service tomcat6 star
8.http://127.0.0.1:8080/
  


files locations


/etc/tomcat6 (this is where the main tomcat config files reside)
/usr/share/doc/usr/share/tomcat6
/usr/share/tomcat6/bin
/usr/share/tomcat6/conf
/usr/share/tomcat6/lib
/usr/share/tomcat6/logs
/usr/share/tomcat6/temp
/usr/share/tomcat6/webapps
/usr/share/tomcat6/work
/var/cache/tomcat6
/var/cache/tomcat6/temp
/var/cache/tomcat6/work
/var/lib/tomcat6 (this is where you will add and/or change most of your files)
/var/lib/tomcat6/webapps
/var/log/tomcat6
